When you come to Madison, you must bring:   Passport  U.S. visa  U.S. Customs and Border Protection  form I-94  If you entered the U.S. before 30 April 2013, the I-94 should be stapled into your passport — do not remove it!  If you entered the U.S. after 30 April 2013, the I-94 is stored electronically;
   you can request a copy to print from CBP  If you are Canadian, you may use a second form of picture ID instead of the I-94 if you did not obtain an I-94.    Additional forms specified in the table below:      If you have this visa  We will also need      F-1 (Student)  Form I-20 (original document, not a copy)    J-1 (Visitor)  Form DS-2019 (original document, not a copy)    Visa Waiver Program  Paper copy of ESTA Authorization     Please bring all required information and documents to the School, especially on Tuesday, July 16.  School staff will
make copies of the documents and return them to you as quickly as possible.  We will announce further details in class.
